{
  "stem": "27507.11",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They talked to us, but they had a job to do, so they went on and there was some shooting during that day-- not an awful lot, but we're so used to shooting.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Shooting went all the time and artillery went all the time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we didn't dare to leave the house on this day, although the Russians were already there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we still didn't feel we were safe to leave the apartment, and we left the apartment only on the day after.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we were then suddenly free.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And when the Germans disappeared on this-- on this day, on the 14th, I remember-- when we realized, because it took us a long time to realize that the Germans were not there anymore-- I went on my knees and I prayed.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The second time.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I prayed-- no, I was so-- I prayed a thanks prayer that I'm allowed to be alive, that I'm allowed to be-- because one was not allowed to be alive.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One was condemned to death, practically, for years.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "For years, one was aware of that-- that any word, any step, anything, is-- is-- practically can kill you.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that was suddenly, one was allowed to live.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One was-- one had suddenly a right to live as a human being.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that was something that was quite earth-shaking.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we left the [PAUSES FOR 2 SECONDS] Koper's flat the day after.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I went with my father, and we spent still about a week or longer in Praga.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And hello?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And spent a week or longer in Praga, and then finally decided to-- my father decided, rather, to move after that more to the east, further from the front.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
